The South Gauteng High Court on Monday declared the South African government's decision to grant former Zimbabwean First Lady Grace Mugabe diplomatic immunity unconstitutional Mugabe allegedly assaulted model Gabriella Engels at a hotel in August last year, but has claimed that she acted in self-defence. She was allowed to leave the country without being prosecuted. But rights group Afriforum and the DA challenged the government’s decision. In May, the International Relations Department argued in court that it did not grant Mugabe diplomatic immunity, but rather recognised it in terms of international law. READ MORE: Minister ‘agonised’ over decision to grant Grace Mugabe diplomatic immunity Judge Bashier Valley said the ministry should pay the costs of the case. – African News Agency